Thank you for that intriguing philosophy on the English language.<br>
<br>
Mark Twain (a.k.a. Samuel Clements) was one of the greatest writers that ever lived. He spelled incorrectly <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>on purpose.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> That's probably what he's most know for, his &quot;writing in dialect,&quot; in books like Huckleberry Finn and Tom Sawyer. Although he is known for many other great books and publications, his greatest two probably contain the most grammatical and spelling errors of any passage ever written.<br>
<br>
I must admit though, I do throw away applications I see from people who cannot write. Resumes and all the like go to the garbage.<br>
