<br>
Its basis is in the literate arts, whereby the purpose of communication is to relay concise thoughts or abstract concepts to another human being.  Language, oft malleable and, dare I say, plastique in nature, still requires protocol, a common agreement to the understanding of terms and symbols between two (or more) parties so folks understand what everyone else is saying.  <br>
<br>
Not limited by nation or origin, language is the basis of the human endeavour, the archetypical mark of the nature of humanity.  Grammar and spelling are not limited to English; rules and form are common in every language on the planet.  <br>
<br>
So, there are rules and such, and they are manifested in the structures of grammar and spelling.  These rules are very useful in the conduct of business, education, arts and literature, law, democracy, music, engineering, traffic management, ad infinitum.  Even in the ancient art of the insult, proper spelling and grammar are crucial.  It is so much more enjoyable when the recipient of said insult understands the full meaning and content of the delivered epithet.  Yes, even in d00dspeak, there is a common understand of proper form of said insult.  Observe a comparative study;<br>
<br>
Proper form of a given insult in d00dspeak;  <br>
<br>
&quot;STFU n00b!&quot;<br>
<br>
Translation;  You, sir/ma'am, are a rank amateur and should cease your mindless drivel at once!<br>
<br>
Improper form;  <br>
<br>
&quot;UFST, 00B&quot;<br>
<br>
Anticpated response from the recipient?  <br>
<br>
&quot;WTF? STFU!&quot;<br>
<br>
Translation;  I beg your pardon?  I cannot understand you!  Please cease and desist with your senseless gibberish!<br>
<br>
So, in summation, proper grammar and spelling are necessary evils in all languages, all methods of communication, in all forums other modicae for the communicative arts.  <br>
<br>
I thank you for your time and attention in this most important and comprehensive subject.  <br>
<br>
Please feel free to consult <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://m-w.com/" target="top">Merriam-Webster Online</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> for all your language needs.  Have an informed day.  <br>
<br>
(translation;  &quot;reed MW and stfu dai n00b, kthxbye~&quot;) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pafuna>Pafuna</A> at: 12/23/02 3:33:51 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=erradicatedthoughts>Erradicated Thoughts</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Egging EW</span><br>  Posts: 388<br> <font color=#628CBC>(12/23/02 4:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=476.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Something Called Protocol</span><hr size=1> Things that make ya say, &quot;Hmmmmm&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=neuromt>Neuro  MT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Giant Squishies in Rathe</span><br>  Posts: 241<br> <font color=#628CBC>(12/23/02 4:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=476.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Something Called Protocol</span><hr size=1> There is a difference between typos and gross abuse of the English language.  I, for one, try not to insult someone's grammatical errors unless they themselves are being grammar nazis, in which case I am mainly pointing out the irony.<br>
